  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 ! \u0b87\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 : \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0bb0\u0b95\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Parliament meets! Filing of nominations for Interim Presidential election today: Secret ballot tomorrow",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "The parliamentary session will be held on Tuesday amid the turmoil in Sri Lankan politics following the resignation of former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa.",
        "Also, the secret ballot to elect the President tomorrow, Wednesday, will be held under the leadership of Parliamentary Secretary General Dammika Dasanayake.",
        "It is a special feature in Sri Lanka's political history that tomorrow will be the day when a President will be elected for the second time through the Parliament.",
        "The parliamentary session will begin today at 10 am under the chairmanship of Speaker Mahinda Yappa Abeywardhana.",
        "In contrast to the usual situation, security has been strengthened in the parliamentary circuit today.",
        "As per article 40 of the constitution following the vacancy of the presidency, the nomination petition will be held today to elect a new president through the parliament.",
        "While the member contesting for the presidential election will officially announce his decision to the Parliamentary Secretary General today, the other person will have to confirm it.",
        "It is mandatory for the candidates who are ready to contest for the presidential election to socialize the assembly today.",
        "Opposition Leader Sajith Premadasa, Acting President Ranil Wickramasinghe, former Minister Dalus Alagaperuma and People's Liberation Front President Anurakumara Dissanayake will contest for the vacant presidency.",
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena has mentioned that the running of more than one candidate during the interim presidential election will pollute the Parliament among the people, and therefore the Freedom Party will not support anyone during this time.",
        "After the assassination of the then President Ranasinghe Premadasa on May 1993, the acting President T. P. Wijatunga was elected as the interim President without a vote in the Parliament.",
        "But as more than one candidate has entered the field, it is noteworthy that according to the constitution, the new president will be chosen tomorrow through a secret ballot in the parliament."
      ],
